FT  20 AUG 93 / UK Company News: Idwal Williams to buy rest of Graig
The scheme of arrangement for Idwal Williams to effect the buy-out of Graig
Shipping shares not already owned by them has been sanctioned and
accordingly the consideration of 157.5p cash per scheme share will be sent
to shareholders in the next week.
Graig's independent directors, Mr Gordon Owen, Mr Peter Tudball and Mr Glyn
Harris, have resigned from the board in line with the agreement announced on
June 15.
